description: For sale: $424,900. Lake Home for Sale on South Lindstrom Lake with Sandy Beach & lake bottom! Chain of Lakes with access to Chisago Lake, North Lindstrom, and recently opened to North and South Center Lakes! Acres of water to explore! Full recreation lakes. Purchased in 2011, the family has completed many updates and tried to preserve as much of the original character as possible. With 5 bedrooms, 2 baths and a walkout basement to finish to your liking, there is plenty of room for family and friends. There have been a lot of updates, Anderson windows, roof, flooring, bathrooms, furnace, well pump, water softener, lighting, interior doors and more. Explore downtown Lindstrom shops, the area vineyards, restaurants, area parks, Franconia Park (kids will love it), skiing, area festivals, and so much more. No need to commute for hours to the cabin when you could be here. Ice is almost off so get your boat ready!

Recently sold: $159,393. Purchase this profitable investment property in a quiet location in Lindstrom within walking distance of bakery, coffee shop, butcher shop, dairy queen, etc. The home is currently utilized as a duplex. Contact owner/agent for more information.

The upper level features 2 bedrooms, 1 full bath, a spacious kitchen with an adjacent dining area, large living room with a brick fireplace, and a sliding door leading to a covered deck.

The  lower level is set up like an apartment featuring one bedroom, a walk-through office/den/2nd bedroom, large living room with brick fireplace, galley-style kitchen with a separate dining area, a full bathroom with its own water heater, a utility/laundry room with washer and dryer, and an additional large unfinished storage room.  The lower level has been recently updated, including newer floor coverings, additional radiant baseboard heat, its own water heater, additional lighting, and refreshed paint.  Outside the front door, there is a covered patio overlooking a private backyard.

description:
Recently sold: $230,000. This excellent three bedroom, 2 ½ bath home has tons of charm and character seldom found in newer construction. Discover a gorgeous hilltop lake view out the front door. There is a pond behind the house nestled in native prairie grasses and flowers that teams with entertaining wildlife.
The main level features, an open floor plan with vaulted ceilings in the great room, a charming corner fireplace in the living room, floors of ¾? solid oak, marble, slate, and/or ceramic tile, two comfortable bedrooms and 1 ½ baths. Kitchen has custom cabinetry and a large pantry. Enjoy a large deck with a ramp. Pocket doors are common. The hardware on these and the custom cabinets on the main level are original Eastlake antiques. Unique lighting throughout. Thoughtful touches like an outlet inside the linen closet of the main bath for rechargeable toothbrushes, shavers, etc.
The walkout level has a large bedroom, spacious family/theater room, large bathroom, and laundry/office.
